This paper deals with the problem of copying machine learning classifiers, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on the theory and framework for copying classifiers, which is related to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the sources of loss and the generation of synthetic sets, which are related to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of classifiers in image recognition (cs.CV) and the need for interpretability and fairness, which are topics in social and information sciences (cs.SI).
